<section class="problem section">
  <div class="container inner">
    <p class="eyebrow scroll-reveal">The problem</p>
    <blockquote class="quote scroll-reveal">
      “Why doesn’t my server talk to Mastodon? Why did Lemmy reject this
      activity?”
    </blockquote>
    <p class="answer scroll-reveal">
      Answering questions like these usually means combining several tools, or
      working from guesswork. When federation breaks, it is hard to tell whether
      the cause is a signature, JSON-LD processing, a WebFinger lookup, or a
      request that never arrived. DrFed brings these stages together in one
      place, so you can see where interoperability breaks down.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .inner {
    max-width: var(--container-narrow);
  }

  .quote {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-weight: 420;
    font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 1.2rem + 2.3vw, 2.9rem);
    line-height: 1.16;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    padding-left: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.6rem);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .answer {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1rem + 0.4vw, 1.25rem);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 40rem;
  }
</style>
